EXTRACTED VALUE: This is not the grand space opera you were looking for.
Not as pointless as it first seems, but dull for anyone not turned on by "Carry On" films. [July 2006, p.72]
While 1942: Joint Strike brings nothing new to its series, it’s just good nostalgic fun when you’ve got a wingman with you.
Ninety-Nine Nights looks fantastic, but it’s not much more than a pretty face.
